Yammy App Privacy Policy

Personal Verification Information

We may collect personal verification information from users in various ways, including when users visit the App, register, place an order, or use other services or features we offer through the App. Users may be asked to provide their name, email address, phone number, and other relevant information as appropriate. We will collect personal verification information from users only if they voluntarily submit such information. Users may have the right to refuse to provide personal verification information, but doing so may result in the inability to engage in certain App-related activities.

Non-Personal Verification Information

We may collect non-personal verification information about users when they interact with the App. Non-personal verification information may include browser name, device type, and technical information about users' means of connection to the App, such as the operating system and Internet service provider used, and other similar information.

How Collected Information Is Used

We may collect and use users' personal information for the following purposes:

Improve customer service: The information you provide helps us respond to your customer service requests and meet your support needs more efficiently. Personalizing User Experience: We may use information to improve and customize your app experience according to your needs and preferences.
Improving and Developing the App: We use information to analyze interactions. The character limit for a single response is 2048, so I'll continue the HTML code in a separate response. Here's the continuation: ```html
Improving and Developing the App: We use information to analyze trends, usage details, and performance to improve and develop our app.
Sending Periodic Emails: If users provide an email address, it may be used to send us relevant information and updates about orders, new products, news, and related products or services. If you do not wish to receive emails from us in the future, you may unsubscribe at any time by contacting us or using the unsubscribe link provided in emails.
Sharing Information with Third Parties

We will not sell, rent, or share user personal information with third parties, except in the following circumstances:

With User Consent: If the user has explicitly consented to the sharing of personal information.
For enforcement and compliance: We reserve the right to disclose users' personal information when we believe in good faith that such disclosure is necessary to comply with the law, enforce our policies, or protect the rights or safety of us or other users.
With Third Party Service Providers: We may share information with third party service providers who provide services on our behalf, such as payment processing, data analytics, or marketing services. These providers are instructed to comply with our Privacy Policy and prohibit the use of the information for other purposes.
Information Security

We take reasonable care to implement appropriate security measures to protect users' personal information. However, we cannot guarantee the absolute security of online information and cannot guarantee the absence of any security breach.

Permanent Account Deletion

We understand that you may wish to permanently delete your account. Please be aware that deleting your account will permanently remove all your data and will not be recoverable.

Steps to Delete Your Account:

1. Log in to the app.

2. Go to the Settings menu.

3. Select Account Information.

4. Tap the Delete Account option.

5. Confirm your desire to delete.

Note:

- All your personal data and activities will be permanently deleted.

- You will not be able to access any content or information associated with your account after deletion.

